    <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>

    <p>Last updated: <strong>August 9, 2025</strong></p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
    <p>By using the dispatch services provided by G&amp;T 5206 Investments, you agree to these Terms &amp; Conditions. If you do not agree, do not use our services.</p>

    <h2>2. Services</h2>
    <p>G&amp;T 5206 Investments provides truck dispatch services including but not limited to load procurement, rate negotiation, carrier packet assistance, and coordination with brokers and shippers.</p>

    <h2>3. Carrier Responsibilities</h2>
    <p>Carriers must maintain appropriate authority, insurance, and licensure. Carriers are responsible for safe operation of equipment and timely communication with G&amp;T dispatch staff.</p>

    <h2>4. Liability &amp; Limitations</h2>
    <p>G&amp;T 5206 Investments acts as a dispatch service and does not assume carrier liability for cargo loss, damage, or accidents. We are not responsible for third-party delays, broker cancellations, or adverse weather.</p>

    <h2>5. Payment &amp; Rate Confirmations</h2>
    <p>Rates agreed between carrier and broker are reflected in the Rate Confirmation (Rate Con). G&amp;T will provide documentation and assist with invoicing; payment terms are governed by the broker/carrier agreement and any factoring arrangements.</p>

    <h2>6. Termination</h2>
    <p>Either party may terminate the dispatch relationship with written notice. Outstanding obligations remain due upon termination.</p>

    <h2>7. Governing Law</h2>
    <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, USA.</p>

    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>For questions about these Terms, contact: <a href="mailto:hashmiumaiz@gmail.com">hashmiumaiz@gmail.com</a>.</p>

